title: [Solhaven, Tucknotch Place]
description: Taking advantage of the solid ground surrounding the base of The Beacon to the southeast, a pristine cottage of wisteria-covered mistwood walls and bevelled window panes nestles at the north end of this cul-de-sac.  Twin gold oil lamps light the doorway, beckoning.

Taking advantage of the span of beachfront to the north of the Beacon, a pristine cottage of wisteria-covered mistwood walls and bevelled window panes nestles at the north end of this cul-de-sac.  Where the ground around it does not sparkle with diamond white sand, it is dotted with patches of bluish-green sweetgrass.  Twin gold oil lamps frame the door, beckoning.
